{
  "stem": "25423.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And my youngest brother, who was born a few years later.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So this was the family.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We had, first of all, a housekeeper and a nanny for the children.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And in addition, every morning a secretary of my father-- who was provided by the Jewish community-- used to come and be there during office hours, equivalent of 9:00",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "00",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That's a very difficult question the question-- because the tendency would be to relate it to the Jewish theological structure here, in the United States, which is orthodox, conservative, and reformed.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was neither.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But after the Haskalah, there were movements in the Jewish community-- in Germany and in Austria, which eventually spilled into Poland-- to [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] adapt the form of worship to different times-- namely, to the emancipation of Jews and no longer existence in ghettos.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You had, in Vienna, this movement-- in Leipzig, in Frankfurt.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they called it enlightened movement or progressive movement.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "In fact, these were orthodox congregations, but with a more formal form of worship.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they were worshiping in, what they referred to, temples.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] The community in Katowice was German-oriented.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And therefore, it was a reflection of the same movement in Germany.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "The community in Lwow was more Vienna-oriented, and reflected the same movement in Vienna.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "My father was an orthodox rabbi.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yes.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I-- I didn't have any direct relationship with the Hasidic movement, but I'm aware of what it was.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Hasidic movements stem from the days of Baal Shem Tov.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They were perverted-- and I use my word specifically and not by accident-- by subsequent evolution of Jewish sects which were headed by dynastic rabbinical families, like [INAUDIBLE], Belz, Sudmore.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And there were [?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Kumarna, ?] [INAUDIBLE], many, many.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, they were everywhere.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
